The paper deals with image aesthetic quality assessment, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves predicting aesthetic attributes captions, which can be seen as a form of natural language processing (NLP) applied to images, thus making cs.MM (multimodal learning) a likely sub-category as well. The use of transfer learning and attention models suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG), while the evaluation criteria used in image captions points towards information retrieval (cs.IR).
